    // Portfolio Grid Section
    section#portfolio
      .container
        .row
          .col-lg-12.text-center
            h2 Portfolio
            |                     
            hr.star-primary
      |         
      .container-fluid
        #custom_carousel.carousel.slide(data-ride='carousel', data-interval='0')
          // Carousel Tab Controls
          .controls
            ul.nav
              li.active(data-target='#custom_carousel', data-slide-to='0')
                a(href='#')
                  p NASA
              | &#x9;&#x9;                
              li(data-target='#custom_carousel', data-slide-to='1')
                a(href='#')
                  p Python
              | &#x9;&#x9;                
              li(data-target='#custom_carousel', data-slide-to='2')
                a(href='#')
                  p Java
              | &#x9;&#x9;                
              li(data-target='#custom_carousel', data-slide-to='3')
                a(href='#')
                  p Web
          // Wrapper for slides
          .carousel-inner
            .item.active
              .container-fluid
                .row
                  .col-md-3
                    img.img-responsive.hidden-xs(src='img/nasa.jpg')
                  | &#x9;&#x9;                        
                  .col-md-9
                    h2 Intern at NASA MSFC
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      | I was an intern for the Deputy Center Chief Technologist at NASA&apos;S Marshall Space Flight Center in Huntsville, Alabama. I worked on building a physical display highlighting the Center&apos;s significant technology achievements.
                    p
                      | In addition to this project, I worked on a side project helping to integrate RCS code for Nanolauncher into a pub/sub framework setup written in C++ and wrapped in lua.
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      | Starting May 2015 I will be a Product Development Intern for Austin-based startup company 
                      a(href='https://www.unboundid.com/', target='_top') UnboundID
                      | .
            |  
            | &#x9;&#x9;            
            .item
              .container-fluid
                .row
                  .col-md-3
                    // What sm and up sees
                    //
                      <div align="center" class="embed-responsive embed-responsive-16by9 hidden-xs"><video align="center" class="embed-responsive-item" preload controls muted ><source src="http://webmup.com/6Bt83/vid.webm"/></video>
                      </div>
                    .hidden-xs(align='center')
                      p Video currently unavailable
                  | &#x9;&#x9;                        
                  .col-md-9
                    h2 Snake Solver
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      a(href='https://github.com/CamelBackNotation/gamejam', target='_top') GitHub
                      | &nbsp;
                      a.visible-xs(href='#snakesolverDemo', data-toggle='modal') Video demo
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      | Snake Solver is a Python game written using the Pygame library during Jolly&apos;s Game Jam. The game is similar to snake except you have to eat the number which solves the equation at the top in order to advance to the next level. The game is 2-player to fit Jolly&apos;s Game Jam theme of &quot;Co-op&quot;.
                    p
                      | The video shows how control of the snake switches between players every 3rd level as depicted by a color change of the snake. This allows each player to trade-off roles of focusing on solving the equation and navigating the snake safely.
                  | &#x9;&#x9;                        
                  .col-md-3
                    // What sm and up sees
                    .embed-responsive.embed-responsive-16by9.hidden-xs(align='center')
                      video.embed-responsive-item(align='center', preload='', controls='')
                        source(src='./img/myo.webm')
                  | &#x9;&#x9;                        
                  .col-md-9
                    h2 Myo-controlled Desktop (Linux)
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      a(href='https://github.com/CamelBackNotation/hackdfw', target='_top') GitHub
                      | &nbsp;
                      a.visible-xs(href='#myoArmband', data-toggle='modal') Video demo
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      | My friend 
                      a(href='http://www.cs.utexas.edu/~pmauldin/') Peter Mauldin
                      |  and I took a 
                      a(href='https://www.thalmic.com/en/myo/') Myo armband
                      | , created custom gestures from raw EMG data, and mapped those gestures to various actions for our computer. The video demo shows off one of our gestures: when the user gives a thumbs up, their music player of choice will open. For me it was Spotify.
                    |  
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      | We also mapped a middle-finger to open our Snake Solver (see above) game, a slightly curled palm thrust forward would open a new tab in Chrome (first opening Chrome if it was not open), and swiping your hand to the right would alt-tab between currently open programs.
            |  
            | &#x9;&#x9;            
            .item
              .container-fluid
                .row
                  .col-md-3.portfolio-item
                    img.img-responsive.hidden-xs(src='img/StockFeed_sm.jpg')
                  | &#x9;&#x9;                        
                  .col-md-9
                    h2 Stock Feed
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      a(href='https://github.com/tireymorris/StockFeed', target='_top') GitHub
                      br
                      a(href='#stockfeedDemo', data-toggle='modal') Video demo
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      | This smartwatch app provides stock and cryptocurrency information to the user. It was developed during HackTX with my group of friends.
                    p
                      | We used a Samsung Galaxy Gear, Bloomberg&apos;s API, and a Microsoft Azure server in order to get the functionality of the app just right. My job was writing the backend using Bloomberg&apos;s API to retrieve stock information.
            |  
            | &#x9;&#x9;            
            .item
              .container-fluid
                .row
                  .col-md-3
                    img.img-responsive.hidden-xs(src='img/website.png')
                  | &#x9;&#x9;                        
                  .col-md-9
                    h2 JoshuaHurt.me
                    | &#x9;&#x9;                            
                    p
                      a(href='https://github.com/CamelBackNotation/less-crappy-website', target='_top') GitHub
                    p
                      | I used Bootstrap to make this website. Bootstrap is an HTML, CSS, and JS framework for developing responsive, mobile first projects on the web. Message me if you find any bugs!
            // End Item
          // End Carousel Inner
        // End Carousel
